    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-06-07T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-06-07T17:00:00-05:00" n="100"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d100">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A4 General Committee/968: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chairman of the American Delegation</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Davis</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-06-07T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 7, 1934—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>428. Your 878, June 6, midnight.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>(1)</label>
                    <item>We of course give you complete discretion in your handling of the question
                        of manufacture of and traffic in arms and consider success in the broader
                        issue of disarmament of greater import than an immediate success in one of
                        its component elements.</item>
                    <label>(2)</label>
                    <item>We agree with you that the French resolution in its present form offers
                        little hope of progress. Nevertheless if as you indicate it is improved to a
                        point where in your judgment (concurred in we hope by the “neutral” Powers)
                        it places disarmament on a parity with security and expresses a
                        determination to proceed with negotiations for actual disarmament, we see no
                        reason for you to oppose it.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
